ProtoDefines:
. "Fix an odd prime $p$. The Gauss sum associated to an 
   integer $a$ is $$ g_a = \sum_{n=1}^{p-1} (\frac{n}{p} ) 
   \zeta^{an}, $$ where $\zeta=\zeta_p = \cos(2\pi{} /p) + i 
   \sin(2\pi{}/p) = e^{2\pi i/p}$."
